library(tidyquant)

returns <- c("BA", "CSCO", "DJIA", "GS", "MMM", "JNJ", "WMT", "JPM", "MCD", "TRV") %>%
    tq_get(get  = "stock.prices",
           from = "2014-1-13", 
           to = "2020-01-13") %>%
    group_by(symbol) %>%
    tq_transmute(select     = adjusted, 
                 mutate_fun = periodReturn, 
                 period     = "daily", 
                 col_rename = "Return")

DJIA <- returns[returns$symbol == "DJIA",] %>% select(Return)
BA <- returns[returns$symbol == "BA",] %>% select(Return)
CSCO <- returns[returns$symbol == "CSCO",] %>% select(Return)
GS <- returns[returns$symbol == "GS",] %>% select(Return)
MMM <- returns[returns$symbol == "MMM",] %>% select(Return)
JNJ <- returns[returns$symbol == "JNJ",] %>% select(Return)
WMT <- returns[returns$symbol == "WMT",] %>% select(Return)
JPM <- returns[returns$symbol == "JPM",] %>% select(Return)
MCD <- returns[returns$symbol == "MCD",] %>% select(Return)
TRV <- returns[returns$symbol == "TRV",] %>% select(Return)
weight_BA = -0.4470
weight_CSCO = 0.4828
weight_GS = -0.4111
weight_MMM= 1.3754

portfolio_1 = BA[2]*weight_BA + CSCO[2]*weight_CSCO + GS[2]*weight_GS + MMM[2]*weight_MMM

portfolio_2 = JPM[2]*(-0.4299) + MCD[2]*0.4301 + TRV[2]*0.9998

portfolio_3 = JNJ[2]*1.275+WMT[2]*(-0.2750)

sqrt(sum(portfolio_1$Return - DJIA$Return)^2 / (length(DJIA$Return) - 1)) * sqrt(252)
## [1] 0.03898336
sqrt(sum(portfolio_2$Return - DJIA$Return)^2 / (length(DJIA$Return) - 1)) * sqrt(252)
## [1] 0.0005216734
sqrt(sum(portfolio_3$Return - DJIA$Return)^2 / (length(DJIA$Return) - 1)) * sqrt(252)
## [1] 0.01987054
p <- ggplot() +
  geom_density(aes(x = portfolio_1$Return, color = '4-asset')) +
  geom_density(aes(x = portfolio_2$Return, color = '3-asset'),linetype = "dashed") +
  geom_density(aes(x = portfolio_3$Return, color = '2-asset'),linetype = "dashed") +
  geom_density(aes(x = DJIA$Return, color = 'DJIA')) +
  xlab("Daily Returns") + ylab("Density") + ggtitle('Daily Returns: DJIA vs. Calculated Portfolios') +
  theme(legend.position = 'right') +
  scale_color_manual(values = c('3-asset' = 'red', '4-asset' = 'blue', 'DJIA' = 'black', '2-asset' = 'orange'))

p <- p + labs(color='Portfolio/Index') 

p

library(tidyverse)
djia <- read_csv("/Users/juanhuml/Desktop/nonparametric_density/djia.csv")
## Parsed with column specification:
## cols(
##   .default = col_double()
## )
## See spec(...) for full column specifications.
djia <- djia[,2:ncol(djia)]
#tickers <- as.data.frame(colnames(djia))
dowmean <- (apply(djia,2,mean))
dowvar <- apply(djia,2,var)
dowskew <- apply(djia,2,skewness)
dowkurt <- apply(djia,2,kurtosis)

moments <- rbind(dowmean, dowvar, dowskew, dowkurt)
moments <- as.data.frame(t(moments))
colnames(moments) <- c("Mean", "Variance", "Skewness", "Kurtosis")
set.seed(420)




df = data.frame(matrix(vector(), 0, 1,
                dimnames=list(c(), c("error"))),
                stringsAsFactors=F)
for (i in 2:15) {
  clusters <- kmeans(moments, i, nstart = 5)
  df[i-1,1] = clusters$tot.withinss
}
clusters <- kmeans(moments, 5, nstart = 1)
series <- 2:15
df <- cbind(df, series)

ggplot(data = df) + geom_line(aes(x = series, y = error)) + xlab("K") + ylab("Error") + theme_light() + theme(axis.text.x=element_text(size=rel(1.25))) + ggtitle("Selection of K for Asset Clustering")

moments$Cluster <- clusters$cluster

clusters
